Greetings, Vespa enthusiasts! Prepare to embark on a festive journey as we bring you the Advent of Tensors. 
In this advent, we'll be diving into the magical world of Vespa Tensors, combining the joy of the holiday season with the power of expressing distributed real-time tensor computations over evolving datasets. 

### ğŸŒŸ What's Vespa Tensors? 
Vespa Tensors, the enchanting framework behind this festive challenge, is not your commodity vector similarity search library. 
Developed by elves close to the North Pole, Vespa Tensors adds a touch of magic to your real-time big data serving use cases, 
offering powerful tensor operations for all your AI real-time serving workloads. Vespa tensors offer much functionality beyond simple similarity search across a single vector representation, enabling features like [multi-vector indexing](https://blog.vespa.ai/semantic-search-with-multi-vector-indexing/) or [feature computations for recommender systems](https://blog.vespa.ai/parent-child-joins-tensors-content-recommendation/)
to name a few AI-powered use-cases using Vespa tensors.

You can learn more about Vespa tensors in the [Vespa tensor user guide](https://docs.vespa.ai/en/tensor-user-guide.html), or if you prefer a blog 
post form: [Computing with tensors in Vespa](https://blog.vespa.ai/computing-with-tensors/). 
All challenges are expressed and solved in the [Vespa tensor playground](https://docs.vespa.ai/playground/) which runs in your browser with zero dependencies. 

### âœ¨ Daily Challenges for 24 Days 
For the next 24 days, we'll unravel a new tensor coding challenge each day, designed to stretch your skills and explore the fascinating capabilities of Vespa Tensors. 
Whether you're a seasoned Vespa expert or a curious beginner, these challenges are sure to spark your interest. Each day, a new challenge will be unlocked in the table below, and the solution to the previous dayâ€™s challenge will be published. 

### ğŸ” Explore the Magic of Tensors

From expressing gift recommendation systems to facial recognition systems for tracking whoâ€™s been nice or naughty, each challenge is a delightful exploration into the capabilities of the Vespa tensor framework. 

### ğŸš€ Spread the Holiday Cheer in Code
